In [156]:
design = MS(Hitters.columns.drop('Salary')).fit(Hitters)
Y = np.array(Hitters['Salary'])
X = design.transform(Hitters)

The ModelSpec (MS) is a design matrix for regression and classification.
Here we are setting up our matrix of X's for the lasso model.
We then create our ouput Y variable as an array.

In [157]:
X_train,X_test, y_train, y_test = skm.train_test_split(X,Y,test_size = 0.2, random_state=43)

Above, we are going to split our data into training and testing sets by 80/20 split.
Next, we are going to set our K Fold Splits. The data will be shuffled befor splitting.
Lastly, we are standarizing the data.

LASSO Model¶

In [158]:
K=10
kfold = skm.KFold(K,
random_state=0,
shuffle=True)
scaler = StandardScaler(with_mean=True,  with_std=True)

Begin our Cross Validation

In [159]:
lassoCV = skl.ElasticNetCV(n_alphas=100, 
                           l1_ratio=1,
                           cv=kfold)
pipeCV = Pipeline(steps=[('scaler', scaler),
                         ('lasso', lassoCV)])
In [160]:

In [161]:
D = design.fit_transform(Hitters)
D = D.drop('intercept', axis=1)
X = np.asarray(D)
Xs = X - X.mean(0)[None,:]
X_scale = X.std(0)
Xs = Xs / X_scale[None,:]

Here we are using our design matrix again, and standarizing our data.

Lasso Model # 2¶

In this model, we will use the same features and interaction terms

In [172]:
import seaborn as sns
from patsy import dmatrices, dmatrix
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.linear_model import LassoCV, ElasticNetCV, RidgeCV
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
In [173]:
formula = ("Salary ~ (AtBat+Hits+HmRun+Runs+RBI+Walks+Years+CAtBat+CHits+CHmRun+CRuns+CRBI+CWalks+League+Division+PutOuts+Assists+Errors+NewLeague)**2 - 1")
y, X = dmatrices(formula, Hitters)
In [174]:
scale_X = StandardScaler().fit(X).transform(X)
scale_y = StandardScaler().fit(y).transform(y)
scale_y = scale_y.ravel()  # ravel collapses a (150, 1) vector to (150,)
In [ ]:
reg_lasso = LassoCV(cv=10).fit(scale_X, scale_y)
In [176]:
EPSILON = 1e-4  # This is to avoid division by zero while taking the base 10 logarithm
plt.figure()
plt.semilogx(reg_lasso.alphas_ + EPSILON, reg_lasso.mse_path_, ':')
plt.plot(reg_lasso.alphas_ + EPSILON, reg_lasso.mse_path_.mean(axis=-1), 'k',
         label='Average across the folds', linewidth=2)
plt.axvline(reg_lasso.alpha_ + EPSILON, linestyle='--', color='k',
            label=r'$\alpha$: CV estimate')
plt.legend()
plt.xlabel(r'$\alpha$')
plt.ylabel('Mean square error')
plt.title('Mean square error on each fold: coordinate descent ')
plt.axis('tight')
plt.show()
